{"id":1501,"date":"2026-07-02T13:11:15","date_gmt":"2026-07-02T12:11:15","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/kleophasindel.github.io\/?page_id=1501"},"modified":"2026-07-09T12:20:20","modified_gmt":"2026-07-09T11:20:20","slug":"crabybot-autonomous-maze-solving-robot","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/kleophasindel.github.io\/crabybot-autonomous-maze-solving-robot\/","title":{"rendered":"Craby&#8217;Bot \u2013 Autonomous Maze-Solving Robot"},"content":{"rendered":"\t\t<div data-elementor-type=\"wp-page\" data-elementor-id=\"1501\" class=\"elementor elementor-1501\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-e7ff27c e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent\" data-id=\"e7ff27c\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c65a7fb elementor-widget elementor-widget-button\" data-id=\"c65a7fb\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"button.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-button-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-button elementor-button-link elementor-size-sm\" href=\"https:\/\/kleophasindel.github.io\/robotic_projects\/\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-content-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-text\">\u2190 Back to Robotics Projects<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-7d92ef9 e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent\" data-id=\"7d92ef9\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-91f4380 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"91f4380\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Craby'Bot - Autonomous Maxe-Solving Robot<\/h2>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c344008 e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent\" data-id=\"c344008\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-7b229b2 e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"7b229b2\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\">\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-0264ffb e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"0264ffb\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-4e3ecc0 elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"4e3ecc0\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"https:\/\/kleophasindel.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/07\/Crabybot_front-1024x683.png\" class=\"attachment-large size-large wp-image-1718\" alt=\"craby&apos;bot front\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kleophasindel.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/07\/Crabybot_front-1024x683.png 1024w, https:\/\/kleophasindel.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/07\/Crabybot_front-300x200.png 300w, https:\/\/kleophasindel.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/07\/Crabybot_front-768x512.png 768w, https:\/\/kleophasindel.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/07\/Crabybot_front.png 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\"  title=\"Craby&#039;Bot \u2013 Autonomous Maze-Solving Robot\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-3dd1370 e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"3dd1370\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\">\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ef01549 e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"ef01549\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-4b364e3 elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"4b364e3\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"https:\/\/kleophasindel.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/07\/Crabybot_back-1024x683.png\" class=\"attachment-large size-large wp-image-1717\" alt=\"craby&apos;bot back\" srcset=\"https:\/\/kleophasindel.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/07\/Crabybot_back-1024x683.png 1024w, https:\/\/kleophasindel.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/07\/Crabybot_back-300x200.png 300w, https:\/\/kleophasindel.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/07\/Crabybot_back-768x512.png 768w, https:\/\/kleophasindel.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/07\/Crabybot_back.png 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\"  title=\"Craby&#039;Bot \u2013 Autonomous Maze-Solving Robot\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-762372c e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent\" data-id=\"762372c\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-5ca7147 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"5ca7147\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>The objective of this project was to design and build an autonomous robot capable of escaping a maze using only an Arduino Uno, two continuous-rotation servos and a single ultrasonic sensor. The mechanical design was entirely custom, requiring us to design, manufacture and assemble a fully functional robot before developing the navigation software.<\/p><p>Working within these hardware constraints required close collaboration between the mechanical and software design, particularly to maximise the capabilities of the single ultrasonic sensor.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8f50869 e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent\" data-id=\"8f50869\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-7c893df elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"7c893df\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Project Information<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c09aea1 e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent\" data-id=\"c09aea1\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-e009d06 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"e009d06\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Duration<\/strong><br \/>November 2023 \u2013 January 2024<\/p><p><strong>Team<\/strong><br \/>5 students<\/p><p><strong>Role<\/strong><br \/>Embedded Programming \u2022 Testing \u2022 Design Collaboration<\/p><p><strong>Technologies<\/strong><br \/>Arduino \u2022 C++ \u2022 Fusion 360 \u2022 3D Printing \u2022 Ultrasonic Sensor<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-535f23e elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"535f23e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">My Contributions<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-5b3cc5a elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"5b3cc5a\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>I mainly contributed to the software development and validation of the robot, while also participating in the design discussions throughout the project.<\/p><p><strong>Programming<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Developed parts of the Arduino software in C++.<\/li><li>Implemented and refined the navigation behaviour.<\/li><li>Tuned motor timings and distance thresholds through iterative testing.<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Testing &amp; Validation<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Tested the robot throughout development.<\/li><li>Identified navigation issues during real-world trials.<\/li><li>Adjusted control parameters to improve reliability and wall-following performance.<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Design Collaboration<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Participated in brainstorming and evaluating different concepts for the robot.<\/li><li>Contributed to selecting the final navigation strategy and mechanical solution.<\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-4b2c264 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"4b2c264\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Engineering Challenge<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-165f908 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"165f908\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>One of the biggest challenges was navigating a maze with only a single fixed ultrasonic sensor.<\/p><p>Several concepts were considered, including periodically rotating the robot to scan its surroundings or positioning the sensor at a 45\u00b0 angle. However, these approaches either reduced navigation accuracy or failed to provide sufficient environmental information.<\/p><p>The final design used a mechanical sliding cover positioned in front of the ultrasonic sensor. As the robot followed the wall, the cover partially blocked the sensor when approaching an obstacle, allowing the robot to distinguish between a wall directly ahead and an opening to the right without adding additional sensors.<\/p><p>This creative mechanical solution allowed the team to overcome the project constraints while keeping the robot simple and lightweight.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c4c75cf elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"c4c75cf\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Navigation Algorithm<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-7852808 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"7852808\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>The robot uses the <strong>right-hand wall-following algorithm<\/strong> to navigate through and escape the maze. The ultrasonic sensor is mounted on the right side of the robot, allowing it to detect and follow the right-hand wall.<\/p><p>Its behaviour follows three simple rules:<\/p><ul><li><p>Turn right when an opening is detected.<\/p><\/li><li><p>Turn left when an obstacle is detected ahead (the ultrasonic sensor is blocked by the crab&#8217;s claw).<\/p><\/li><li><p>Otherwise, continuously adjust its trajectory to maintain a constant distance from the right-hand wall.<\/p><\/li><\/ul><p>Throughout development, repeated testing was carried out to optimise the distance thresholds and motor timings, improving the robot&#8217;s stability despite slight performance differences between the two drive motors.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-65c6452 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"65c6452\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Testing &amp; Optimisation<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c13cfdb elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"c13cfdb\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Testing played an important role throughout the project.<\/p><p>Rather than relying solely on simulation, the robot was repeatedly tested on physical maze sections to identify practical issues that could not be predicted during development.<\/p><p>These included:<\/p><ul><li>Drift caused by unequal motor performance.<\/li><li>Inconsistent ultrasonic measurements near corners.<\/li><li>Fine-tuning turning durations and wall-following behaviour.<\/li><\/ul><p>Each test cycle was used to refine the software until the robot could reliably navigate the maze.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-5d421af elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"5d421af\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Results<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-734f415 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"734f415\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>The final prototype successfully demonstrated:<\/p><p>\u2714 Autonomous maze navigation<\/p><p>\u2714 Fully 3D-printed custom robot<\/p><p>\u2714 Reliable wall-following using a single ultrasonic sensor<\/p><p>\u2714 Embedded control using Arduino<\/p><p>\u2714 Iterative development through testing<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-f3751af elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"f3751af\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">What I Learned<\/h3>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-aed035b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"aed035b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>This project gave me my first experience of developing software for a physical robotic system, where testing and iteration were just as important as programming.<\/p><p>I learned how to translate a navigation strategy into embedded code, validate it on real hardware and continuously refine the robot&#8217;s behaviour through experimentation. It also showed me how mechanical design and software can complement each other when solving engineering problems under strict hardware constraints.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>\u2190 Back to Robotics Projects Craby&#8217;Bot &#8211; Autonomous Maxe-Solving Robot The objective of this project was to design and build an autonomous robot capable of escaping a maze using only an Arduino Uno, two continuous-rotation servos and a single ultrasonic sensor. The mechanical design was entirely custom, requiring us to design, manufacture and assemble a [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"site-sidebar-layout":"no-sidebar","site-content-layout":"page-builder","ast-site-content-layout":"full-width-container","site-content-style":"default","site-sidebar-style":"default","ast-global-header-display":"","ast-banner-title-visibility":"","ast-main-header-display":"","ast-hfb-above-header-display":"","ast-hfb-below-header-display":"","ast-hfb-mobile-header-display":"","site-post-title":"","ast-breadcrumbs-content":"","ast-featured-img":"disabled","footer-sml-layout":"","ast-disable-related-posts":"","theme-transparent-header-meta":"","adv-header-id-meta":"","stick-header-meta":"","header-above-stick-meta":"","header-main-stick-meta":"","header-below-stick-meta":"","astra-migrate-meta-layouts":"default","ast-page-background-enabled":"default","ast-page-back